	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		"   'Tis not fair. Not one bit. I was hired to be the one what fixes the buildings and keeps it all tip top. What right does Hales have to make me do the bleedin' cooking? It's not my fault Roland up and scarpered "
		" now, is it?"
		""
		"   Not surprised he did, mind you. Saw him coming from the hallway the other night, white as a sheet. Like a man what has looked into the very pits "
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		"of hell itself. I know them street sods aren't a pretty sight, but m'lord says they's being moved to a place of work, so that can't be it. I wonder what Roland could have saw to make him go so white in the face? Heard him crying in his room later. All night it went on. Then the drinking started and now he's   gone."
		""
		"   We's supposed to stay in our rooms when them Daltons "
	}
	"page2_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		"are moving people about, so it should be Roland in the kacky, not me! I'm not the one what broke the rules. And why do I have to do the bleedin' cooking for the nobs upstairs, also? They's fancy staff, so let them get they "
		" own fancy cook!"
		""
		""
	}
	"page2_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_right_body"	:
	{
		""
	}
