readables/man2/note_twistleton_to_hales
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "3"
	"page1_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_body"	:
	{
		""
		"  Hales,"
		""
		"    I trust you to have taken care of it, but I am nevertheless unsettled by the fact that a common thief took it upon himself to start sniffing about down there. I am certain the arrival of a Watch Captain is not a coincidence. From now on I want that trapdoor locked at all times. Your Dalton brothers will simply have to stay down there until this troublesome Captain is convinced to move along. I have sent word "
	}
	"page2_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_body"	:
	{
		""
		"to P, who will no doubt act with alacrity to instruct the Watch Commander to bring his disobedient terrier to heel. I'll inform you when it is safe to resume activities."
		""
		"    In the interim I'd like you to do what you do so well and have a quiet word with that pompous prick, Percy. He's the new tenant in Highclere House. The fool stays up all night inscribing his silly \"introspections\" and has now taken notice of the gaol wagon arriving to collect the unfortunates."
	}
	"page3_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page3_body"	:
	{
		""
		" He still believes it to be comprised of \"drunken peasants\" and has taken it upon himself to \"instruct\" me to do something about the noise. The little shit. Still, we can't afford any further attention, or you and I will both find ourselves shoved in the wagon too! I suppose then we'll finally discover where they're all being "
		" transported to."
		""
		"   T"
		""
	}
	"gui_page1"	: "guis/readables/scrolls/scroll_calig_mac_humaine.gui"
	"gui_page2"	: "guis/readables/scrolls/scroll_calig_mac_humaine.gui"
