readables/man2/journal_roland
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "3"
	"page1_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_body"	:
	{
		"    Oh Builder forgive me, my own daughter. To see you living upon the streets these years past, so ashamed was I that I turned my head and hurried away. So ashamed am I still. 'Twas you that felt my belt when your mother left us. 'Twas you that felt my fists."
		""
		"   Suffer me beyond death, for those times are nothing compared to the night gone by when I cracked the hallway door and saw you pushed"
	}
	"page2_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_body"	:
	{
		"along with all the others. The poor and the weak. Led to that hell beyond the trapdoor by those merciless thugs. "
		""
		"   You saw me. You recognised me. And I watched all hope vanish from your face, as you would have known for certain that your own papa would not lift a finger to help you."
		""
		"   So ashamed am I.  "
		"   I watched and I did nothing."
		""
		""
		""
		""
		""
	}
	"page3_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page3_body"	:
	{
		"   I am a coward and I shall meet "
		"a coward's end. I shan't ever see you again, my daughter, for if there is life after death I shall be going to a different place than thee."
		""
		"   Builder forgive me."
		""
		"   Roland"
	}
