readables/man2/journal_twistleton
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "3"
	"page1_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		"    They believe me a fool, the lot of them. But was it not I who discovered an inn built above a disused mine? Is it not I who has now more than doubled his quota? Can any of the others in Bridgeport say the same? If I am a fool then why did P choose me to oversee this sector? Not to mention entrusting me with hosting the Moor liaison?"
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		" "
		"     Yet they send a spy to masquerade as my secretary, to watch me as though they doubt my competence. The sheer arrogance of it, as if a life in the sewers hadn't taught me to smell a rat "
		" among the kacky."
		""
		"     Nevertheless, I must remove my Harriet from this danger and move on. Soon I "
	}
	"page2_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		"shall be forced to take my hidden valuables and start afresh, somewhere far away from this forsaken city and the likes of P and his \"Provident Order\". They were not raised on these streets as I was. They have not thought this through."
		""
		"     Soon the Builders are going to get involved, for it is their forges that are most"
	}
	"page2_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		"in need of coal. Say what you like about those zealots, but they do not put up with nonsense. They'll likely cave P's skull in when they learn the truth, and I for one intend to be a long way away when that happens."
		""
		"     Besides, I do not have the "
		"stomach for this. I cannot see the unfortunates as cattle the way Hales does. And to think  "
	}
	"page3_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page3_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		"it was I who convinced P to hire her. In my former life I'd noted her ruthlessly efficient hatred towards street dwellers, though I am not certain from whence it stems. Perhaps she herself was once a victim of some sort?  I dare not ask. "
		"If my time as a smuggler taught me anything, it was how to avoid a certain type "
		" of copper."
		""
		""
	}
	"page3_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page3_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		"     Such a pretty, hateful"
		"  creature."
		""
	}
