		"  COAL SHORTAGE WORSENS"
	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"    Mayor Goddard has warned of yet another increase to the coal price, as \"the shortage will likely extend further than initially expected.\" A number of Bridgeport residents and small business owners have already complained of suffocating price hikes that have placed undue strain upon public wellbeing and profits. The Mayor went on to assure those who gathered in protest that they would \"not be deprived of coal, only required to pay a little more for it.\" "
		"When pressed to provide an answer as to "
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		"what sum he considered to be \"a little more\", Mayor Goddard replied that \"the city's leadership will always prioritise the pockets of the people first,\" and further pleaded for the gathered souls to quietly return to their homes."
		"\"Fat bloody chance,\" said city resident Mauldy Creviss, who wished to remain anonymous."
		""
		"Updates to the coal price will be published daily by the Bridgeport Review."
		""
	}
