	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"    A spate of mysterious disappearances of street dwellers has prompted Commander Fleeting of the City Watch to pass public comment. He states that the number of missing persons has been greatly exaggerated by the public, and warns against \"jumping to "
		" conclusions\" as to the cause of the issue."
		" "
		"  When asked if the City Watch had opened an investigation into the disappearances, "
		"the Commander replied that details of the case were not for public knowledge. "
		"  Lord Pottinger of the Bankers' Guild then"
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"took to the podium in order to applaud the City Watch for a marked decrease in crime. He attributed the recently published crime report to \"fine police work,\" before going on to deny that any such drop in crime could possibly be related to the dwindling number of poor residents, stating \"I hadn't noticed any were missing, since I rarely notice them "
		" at all.\""
	}
