		""
		"    Good, you've made it this far without arousing suspicion."
		"    Before he disappeared, Jacobs managed "
		"to report that street dwellers had been lured into the underbelly of this very inn after dark, never to be seen again. He is not the first to have noticed such misdeeds taking place across the city, but he is the first to have identified one of the dark holes into which they appear to have vanished."
		""
		"    Jacobs had specifically informed me of which room he had rented and I therefore searched it thoroughly upon my arrival.  "
		""
	}
	"page2_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"    Please take this key that was hidden here. "
		"I believe he intended it for you, though I am fearful of what you may find at the end of where it leads. "
		""
		"   Since my presence at the inn will have given cause to halt any untoward activities hereabouts, it is imperative that you now find out what happened to him. "
		""
		"   Also see what you can dig up about one Lord Twistleton, owner of the tenancy attached to the inn, called Highclere House. "
		" He resides in the large home across the"
	}
	"page3_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page3_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"street. The man is surely involved and no doubt keeps a journal, which I would also like you to acquire for me."
		""
		"    W."
		""
		"     PS. Remember, do not attempt to speak to me in this place. We will meet another time."
		""
	}
