		"My dearest Harriet,"
		""
		"     Allow me the small grace of providing an explanation in writing, as words so often fail me when standing before you. Even after all these years you hold such power over me, my love. "
		""
		"     I do not disagree with you with regards the treatment of the unfortunates, but as you well know I have little choice in the matter. It was either this or a criminal sentence, if you recall? That ghastly P and his so-called \"Provident Order\" are the very bankers and lawmakers that rule this city. "
		" To cross them is to court the noose. "
		""
		"   In reply to your question over breakfast,"
		""
		"   "
	}
	"page2_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_body"	:
	{
		"which I so rudely ignored, the answer is yes. I do remember our first meeting and I think of it often. You with a sword to my back upon my entering your turf unbidden! Hah, what a pair we made. They called me the Smuggler King, but you and I both know I would have achieved nought in the absence of the strength of my most capable partner. You were my everything then, and so you "
		" are still."
		""
		"     We shall be gone from this place soon. "
		"I have now resolved to hasten our imminent departure. We shall be free again, my love. Will you please bear with me a little while "
		"  longer?"
		""
		"    T"
	}
